Kubernetes Probes
-----------------
Readiness Probe - Controls when traffic is allowed, If this fails → pod removed from Service endpoints
Liveness Probe - Checks if app is alive, If fails → Kubernetes restarts pod
Startup Probe - Used for slow starting apps (like DB, JVM) Prevents premature restarts

Protocols
---------
HTTP probe (most common) - Kubernetes sends an HTTP request to your container. 200–399 → healthy ✅
TCP probe (basic connectivity) - Kubernetes just checks port is open. Connection success → healthy ✅
Exec probe (run command inside container) - Kubernetes runs a command inside container. Exit code 0 → healthy ✅

Common health check paths
-------------------------
/health → generic health check ✅
/healthz → Kubernetes-style health check
/ready → readiness check
/readyz → readiness (K8s convention)
/live → liveness check
/livez → liveness (K8s convention)
/status → app status
/ping → simple alive check
/metrics → sometimes used (Prometheus + health)